A leading aspirant for the position of national chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Senator Mohammed Sani Musa, has paid a visit to the governor of Gombe State, Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya, at the Gombe State Governorâ€™s lodge in Abuja. The visit was in continuation of his consultation with stakeholders and leaders within the party.  Musa and Yahaya spoke extensively on ways to move the party forward, especially with regards to the March 26 convention of the party. While presenting his agenda for the party, if elected, Musa said he is prepared to bring about visionary leadership to the APC and rejig the entire party architecture, in line with international best practices. In his remarks, Yahaya said APC deserves the best hand to manage its affairs at this time and that he is convinced Musa possesses the right leadership qualities for the job. He urged Musa to continue with his consultations to all party leaders and prayed for his successful outing at the convention, stressing that he will be looking forward to working with him if he emerges next national chairman. 